</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/37378766-mike-c">Mike C</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Considering the book is fundamentally about the relationship between two men during war time, I think there are a couple of well rounded female charac<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Considering the book is fundamentally about the relationship between two men during war time, I think there are a couple of well rounded female characters - Michiko, Isabel, and several lesser ones such Aunt Mai, Ming and the ghost of Philip's mother - if there were more women characters and they played a more prominent role in the book, then it would be a different story.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
