<span id="freeTextContainer15463810155345169322">DNF. <br/> <br/>I tried about 75 pages of this over the last week and it is not doing anything for me for the following reasons:<br/> <br/>1. This is a slow-build of a novel at a time when I am not in the mood for a slow-paced, potentially over-written story.<br/> <br/>2. Although the story is set in Penang and I have an interest in the place, it seems to be rather similar to Tan Twan Eng&apos;s second book The Garden of Evening Mists, which also deals with a WWII setting. <br/> <br/>3. I have a feeling that I can guess where this story is</span>
  <span id="freeText15463810155345169322" style="display:none">DNF. <br /> <br />I tried about 75 pages of this over the last week and it is not doing anything for me for the following reasons:<br /> <br />1. This is a slow-build of a novel at a time when I am not in the mood for a slow-paced, potentially over-written story.<br /> <br />2. Although the story is set in Penang and I have an interest in the place, it seems to be rather similar to Tan Twan Eng's second book The Garden of Evening Mists, which also deals with a WWII setting. <br /> <br />3. I have a feeling that I can guess where this story is going, and if I am right, it will be very similar to The Harmony Silk Factory. Too similar for my liking. <br /> <br />So, I am going to set this one aside for a book that does not feel like a repetition right now.<br /> <br />No rating.</span>
