<div id="review_55093506" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/55093506" />
    <a title="Jeanette (Ms. Feisty)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/796425-jeanette-ms-feisty"><img alt="Jeanette (Ms. Feisty)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1304653755p2/796425.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/55093506?book_show_action=true">May 05, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeanette (Ms. Feisty)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeanette (Ms. Feisty)" href="/user/show/796425-jeanette-ms-feisty">Jeanette (Ms. Feisty)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781602860742" href="/book/show/6325666-the-gift-of-rain">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/796425-jeanette-ms-feisty?shelf=asia">asia</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/796425-jeanette-ms-feisty?shelf=world-war-two-fiction">world-war-two-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/796425-jeanette-ms-feisty?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/796425-jeanette-ms-feisty?shelf=four-star-fiction">four-star-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/796425-jeanette-ms-feisty?shelf=all-fiction">all-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer55093506" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5495179276825341530">The setting is the island of Penang, off the coast of Malaya. The population is a complex mix of races, ideologies, and income levels. Chinese, Japanese, Malays, British, Indians, and many people of mixed race share this tiny island and have a history of tensions and race/class divisions. However, they&apos;ve managed to find ways to live together in relative harmony.<br/><br/>When the Japanese occupy the island during World War II, concerns for personal and family safety lead to treachery and betrayal among t</span>
  <span id="freeText5495179276825341530" style="display:none">The setting is the island of Penang, off the coast of Malaya. The population is a complex mix of races, ideologies, and income levels. Chinese, Japanese, Malays, British, Indians, and many people of mixed race share this tiny island and have a history of tensions and race/class divisions. However, they've managed to find ways to live together in relative harmony.<br /><br />When the Japanese occupy the island during World War II, concerns for personal and family safety lead to treachery and betrayal among the inhabitants, even among friends. The racial and ideological divisions become more pronounced and cause people to turn on one another, with devastating results. <br /><br />By the end of the novel, you will no doubt feel that some of the characters made very wrong choices. But you'll also be hard pressed to say for sure what would have been better choices under the circumstances. The narrator, Philip Hutton, tells the story at the age of 75, looking back more than 50 years to the time of the events. He was barely more than a boy during the war, but he has never been able to forgive himself for the decisions he made and the heartache they caused.<br /><br />This book really made me think about gray areas and tough choices. We'd all like to think we would do the right thing in a difficult situation. But what if doing the right thing for your family means misery and death for many other innocent people? And what if trying to rectify your mistakes could potentially make things worse, and even lead to your own death? </span>
  <a data-text-id="5495179276825341530" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


