<div id="review_2218337725" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2218337725" />
    <a title="T.D. Whittle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6051061-t-d-whittle"><img alt="T.D. Whittle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1532773499p2/6051061.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2218337725?book_show_action=true">Dec 18, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="T.D. Whittle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="T.D. Whittle" href="/user/show/6051061-t-d-whittle">T.D. Whittle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781905802142" href="/book/show/18489148-the-gift-of-rain">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6051061-t-d-whittle?shelf=reviews">reviews</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6051061-t-d-whittle?shelf=tan-twan-eng">tan-twan-eng</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2218337725" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5037787502714639494">Here, at the eleventh hour, I am happy to declare <i>The Gift of Rain</i> my favourite read of 2017. (I&apos;m excluding <i>War and Peace</i> because it seems unfair not to. I consider Tolstoy to occupy his own realm entirely.) I was utterly captivated by this book and so tense during the final third that my shoulders and back began to ache. I finished it at three o&apos;clock this morning, and my sweet husband massaged the knots out of my body so that I could sleep. (I am not very practised at zazen, as you may have g</span>
  <span id="freeText5037787502714639494" style="display:none">Here, at the eleventh hour, I am happy to declare <i>The Gift of Rain</i> my favourite read of 2017. (I'm excluding <i>War and Peace</i> because it seems unfair not to. I consider Tolstoy to occupy his own realm entirely.) I was utterly captivated by this book and so tense during the final third that my shoulders and back began to ache. I finished it at three o'clock this morning, and my sweet husband massaged the knots out of my body so that I could sleep. (I am not very practised at zazen, as you may have guessed.) We have already reached the final day of 2017 here in Australia, and I am so pleased to have randomly selected this book to complete my year.<br /><br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/439411060?book_show_action=false&amp;from_review_page=1" rel="nofollow noopener">Samadrita's review</a> reflects my own thoughts and feelings so perfectly and eloquently, that I see no reason to add my own lengthy review. Just read hers and I will nod along saying, yes that's it, precisely. Yes, me too, me too. It is a book to cherish. Brutal and beautiful, all at the same time. <br /><br />My first book of 2018 is going to be <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12031532.The_Garden_of_Evening_Mists" title="The Garden of Evening Mists by Tan Twan Eng" rel="nofollow noopener">The Garden of Evening Mists</a> which is sitting here waiting for me, and I am already a bit disappointed that it looks half the length of the first. I seem to be enjoying long reads these days, even more so than usual.<br /><br />Happy New Year, fellow readers!</span>
  <a data-text-id="5037787502714639494" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


