<div id="review_2005080756" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2005080756" />
    <a title="DeB" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9827967-deb"><img alt="DeB" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1637908590p2/9827967.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2005080756?book_show_action=true">May 18, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="DeB" class="user" itemprop="url" name="DeB" href="/user/show/9827967-deb">DeB</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9827967-deb?shelf=africa-mideast-asia">africa-mideast-asia</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9827967-deb?shelf=memorably-good">memorably-good</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9827967-deb?shelf=war-stories">war-stories</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9827967-deb?shelf=dramatic-fiction">dramatic-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9827967-deb?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2005080756" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16194856315247934101">I adored Tan Twan Eng’s second novel, “The Garden of the Evening Mists”. The language was so beautiful it made me ache at times. It is a huge story, intricately plotted, deeply emotional and one of the best books that I have ever read. <br/><br/>“The Gift of Rain” was nominated for a Booker Prize, and I expected to be swept along by it as I had been by Eng’s second novel. It does share a similar dream-like atmosphere, and at its historical centre are the atrocities committed by the Japanese during World W</span>
  <span id="freeText16194856315247934101" style="display:none">I adored Tan Twan Eng’s second novel, “The Garden of the Evening Mists”. The language was so beautiful it made me ache at times. It is a huge story, intricately plotted, deeply emotional and one of the best books that I have ever read. <br /><br />“The Gift of Rain” was nominated for a Booker Prize, and I expected to be swept along by it as I had been by Eng’s second novel. It does share a similar dream-like atmosphere, and at its historical centre are the atrocities committed by the Japanese during World War II in Malaysia. It too is rich with its descriptions of the Asian culture, those of Western origin who lived and loved the country and the conflicting feelings around the colonial empires that made fortunes through trade. <br /><br />Don’t get me wrong - “The Gift of Rain” is an exquisite novel. The writing is so good that it spoiled me for the next couple of books which came after. Eng is so talented, that it takes ones’ breath away... <br /><br />I’m a greedy soul, though, and not fair to Eng because I wanted to be transported in equal measure to “The Garden of the Evening Mists”, and I wasn’t quite. <br /><br />In the world of movies, this would be a Golden Globe. Darned excellent. Unfortunately, I experienced his second novel first - and it won an Oscar. <br /><br />“The Gift of Rain” is 4.5 stars... but I’ll rate it at four here, because, yes, I’m still measuring it against “The Garden of the Evening Mists”.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16194856315247934101" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


